text: Dirk Else (born 27 August 1977 in Erlabrunn, GDR) is a retired German ski jumper. In the World Cup he finished once among the top 15, a twelfth place from Zakopane in January 2002 being his best result. He won the overall Continental Cup in the 1999/00 season. ==External links== * Category:1977 births Category:Living people Category:People from Erzgebirgskreis Category:German male ski jumpers
